            "en": "Large TV OLED manufacturing line depreciation is structurally winding down through 2025–2026, reducing fixed-cost headwinds materially. Korea Ratings assessed that this depreciation tail-off, combined with stabilizing small-to-medium OLED technology, would continue to drive profitability improvement. The simultaneous exit from low-margin LCD models and expansion of OLED revenue share (from 54% in 2024 toward an estimated 64% in 2026) have driven area-based ASP up 55% year-on-year, confirming the structural upgrade in quantitative terms. Even during the Q1 2026 seasonal slow period, EBITDA margin reached 20.6%, and profit improvement is expected to accelerate further in the seasonally stronger second half."
