            "en": "At KRW 166,700 on June 4, 2026, the share price is approximately 264% above the 52-week low and trades at an 80%-plus premium to DS Securities' recently upgraded target of KRW 92,000. The re-rating is almost entirely event-driven — NVIDIA collaboration news, Jensen Huang's visit, physical AI thematic momentum — while the underlying NVIDIA partnership remains at a non-binding discussion stage with no revenue recognition confirmed. PBR of ~14.5x on an FY2025 basis is stretched even for a pre-profit high-growth narrative, implying minimal margin of safety. Should any of the anticipated catalysts fail to convert into concrete agreements or product revenue, a sharp mean-reversion correction remains a material risk."
