            "en": "Samsung Electronics alone accounted for approximately 55–56% of total revenue as of Q3 2025, creating a significant single-customer concentration risk. Any delay or scale-back in Samsung's memory capex plans could cause Wonik IPS's quarterly results to fall materially below consensus, as evidenced by the dramatic swing in Samsung-related revenue from KRW 58.3 billion in Q1 2025 to KRW 202.2 billion in Q2 2025. An expansion of Samsung's in-house equipment subsidiary SEMES could further reduce the share of capex allocated to external suppliers like Wonik IPS. Until overseas customer diversification accelerates meaningfully, this concentration risk is structurally difficult to mitigate."
