            "en": "A reported manufacturing utilization rate of approximately 16% (per the 2025 annual report) means the company must absorb an estimated KRW 200 billion annually in fixed costs—salaries and depreciation—even during slow periods. If end-market conditions deteriorate or customer purchase orders dry up, the reverse operating leverage effect could rapidly push operating profit back below breakeven. It is critical to recall that Wonik IPS posted an operating loss of approximately KRW 18 billion in 2023 and achieved only minimal operating income of approximately KRW 11 billion in 2024—both just two to three years ago. Unless structural improvements in utilization accompany revenue growth, the current earnings recovery carries latent reversal risk in the next cyclical downturn."
