            "en": "Foreign visitor spending at Lotte's department stores set an all-time quarterly record of over 700 billion KRW in Q4 2025, with same-store sales up approximately 8% and foreign customer sales up 37% for the quarter, signaling that inbound demand has become a structural earnings driver. The recovery in Chinese consumer confidence, yuan appreciation, and normalization of inbound Korean tourism all represent incremental demand tailwinds, and Q1 2026 department store operating profit of 191 billion KRW (+47.1% YoY) confirmed the trend's durability. Expansion of high-margin fashion categories is amplifying operating leverage as fixed costs are spread over a growing revenue base, and Hanwha Investment Securities expects double-digit same-store growth to continue through the second half of 2026. The TimVillas complex mall strategy, once fully deployed, should create a more powerful experiential platform capable of attracting both international visitors and domestic millennials, sustaining long-term foot traffic gains."
