        "en": "For full-year 2025, E-Mart's consolidated operating profit surged 584.8% to KRW 322.5 billion from KRW 47.1 billion in the prior year, while net income turned positive at KRW 246.3 billion after a KRW 573.4 billion net loss in 2024. Consolidated revenue of KRW 28.97 trillion declined marginally by 0.2% year-on-year, reflecting the structural headwinds in the hypermarket sector, but the dramatic improvement in profitability signals effective cost discipline and subsidiary-level earnings recovery. The operating profit surge benefited partly from a low base effect, as 2024 had included a one-time charge of approximately KRW 213.2 billion in retirement benefit provisions. On a standalone basis, E-Mart's own hypermarket recorded total sales of KRW 17.97 trillion (+5.9%) and operating profit of KRW 277.1 billion (+127.5%), demonstrating that the core retail business is recovering meaningfully. In Q1 2026, consolidated operating profit reached KRW 178.3 billion (+11.9% YoY), the highest Q1 result in 14 years since 2012's KRW 190.5 billion, even as consolidated revenue edged down 1.3% to KRW 7.12 trillion. The space-innovation strategy is delivering tangible results: the Ilsan, Dongtang, and Gyeongsan stores, refurbished in the Starfield Market format, saw sales increase by 75.1%, 12.1%, and 18.5% respectively versus the prior year. The flagship discount campaign 'Goraeit Festa' attracted 23 million participants in 2025, driving a 28.1% sales increase during the campaign period, underscoring the effectiveness of E-Mart's price leadership strategy. The share price peaked around KRW 106,200 on the day of the Q1 2026 earnings release (May 13) but has since retraced to KRW 88,400 as of June 4, 2026, entering a technical consolidation phase."
