        "en": "E-Mart has set its 2026 consolidated net revenue guidance at KRW 29.3 trillion (+1.1%), though the market is scrutinizing this figure given that actual 2025 revenue missed the prior-year guidance of KRW 30.3 trillion by 4.4%. Achieving the medium-term Value-Up targets of KRW 34 trillion in revenue and KRW 1 trillion in operating profit by 2027 will require aggressive top-line growth over the next two years, with Traders' store expansion (targeting over 6.6% growth) and SSG.com's path to profitability serving as pivotal variables. On the regulatory front, the amendment to the Distribution Industry Development Act permitting large-mart dawn delivery is under parliamentary review and could act as a medium-term catalyst by enabling E-Mart's nationwide stores to function as logistics hubs for omni-channel services. However, industry participants caution that the near-term earnings impact of regulatory relief will be limited given the steep logistics and labor cost hurdles and Coupang's entrenched position in the dawn-delivery market. The most significant uncertainty is the unresolved brand controversy at Starbucks Korea (SCK Company); if the situation leads to a license termination or deconsolidation, E-Mart would face a meaningful hole of approximately KRW 173 billion annually in operating profit contribution. On the upside, the RMN (Retail Media Network) business and investments in AI infrastructure represent emerging non-traditional revenue streams that could diversify the earnings base, while the grocery-specialization and price-leadership strategy continues to drive customer count growth and repeat visits."
