        "en": "Looking toward H2 2026, the visibility of OCI Holdings' earnings recovery is improving. Sell-side estimates indicate that from Q2 onward, normalization of OCI TerraSus operations combined with profit recognition from OCI Energy's 500MW solar project divestiture will steepen the operating income recovery curve. In H2, the ramp-up of Vietnam Neo Silicon wafer shipments and polysilicon ASP increases tied to the finalization of U.S. Section 232 tariff measures should provide additional earnings leverage. Should the SpaceX supply agreement be officially confirmed, an estimated 8,000–11,000 tons per year of new volume could be allocated within the existing 35,000-ton capacity footprint, potentially triggering an accelerated capacity expansion decision. Over the medium term, the Texas solar cell plant's expected IRA AMPC qualification would support profitability improvement in the energy solutions segment. In the near term, however, additional supply agreements are structurally difficult to translate directly into quarterly earnings without prior capacity additions, and global polysilicon pricing trends and the pace of chemicals segment recovery remain critical variables."
