        "en": "The pivotal question for 2026 is whether KT's organic AI- and cloud-driven profit growth can fill the earnings gap left by the expiry of one-time real estate development gains. If KT Cloud, AICC, and data-centre revenues maintain their current trajectories, the scale of earnings normalisation may be contained—but with the Microsoft partnership yet to demonstrate clear revenue traction, the pace of AI monetisation remains a key variable to monitor. Under CEO Park Yoon-young, KT is rationalising 23 low-growth/non-core businesses and restructuring 16 low-profitability operations; successful execution through FY2028 should unlock meaningful portfolio-efficiency improvements. On the 6G front, Pre-6G technology development is underway from 2026 targeting 2030 commercialisation, with an AI-native network vision and multi-orbit satellite expansion through KT SAT representing credible long-term growth optionality. Kbank's decision to re-pursue an IPO is a medium-term potential catalyst for unlocking embedded value within the group. Against these positives, intensifying marketing competition, regulatory tariff-reduction pressure, and persistent cybersecurity risks remain ongoing headwinds to near-term profitability. In sum, 2026 is a transitional year of earnings normalisation, and the extent to which KT builds an AICT monetisation track record during this period will be the decisive factor shaping its eventual valuation re-rating."
